FBIS3-13804 "drnes054dd_94010" FBIS-NES-94-054 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Mar 1994 Palestinian Affairs Opposition Groups React to UN Resolution 904 DFLP Criticizes Hebron Resolution JN1903125094 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1200 GMT 19 Mar 94 JN1903125094 Paris Radio Monte Carlo Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] The Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP] regards the new U.S. attitude toward the UN Security Council resolution as a disturbing retreat from the stands adopted by previous U.S. Administrations. The front called Resolution No. 904 weak and colorless with no firm decisions on protecting the Palestinian people. The Islamic Resistance Movement, Hamas, rejected the resolution and considered it insufficient and incomplete. Hamas voiced its disappointment with the stands of the Arab sides, including that of the PLO.
